# Java Standards

## Dependency Injection

- Use **constructor injection** for services and business logic beans
- Field injection (`@Inject`) is acceptable for **Picocli commands** (`Runnable` / command classes)
- Annotate services with `@ApplicationScoped`, config/producers with `@Singleton` where appropriate
- **MapStruct `@Named` helpers** used by mappers: `@ApplicationScoped` beans in `mapping.fields` (constructor-inject `Logger` when logging is needed)

## Data Classes

- Use **Java records** for DTOs and value objects (e.g. `model.csv.Repository`, `model.graphql.GitHubRepoStatsGraphqlData`)
- Use Apache Commons Lang3 (`EqualsBuilder`, `HashCodeBuilder`, `CompareToBuilder`) in records when custom equality/ordering is needed
- Add `@RegisterForReflection` to records and classes required for **Quarkus native** (including MapStruct mapping beans and hand-written GraphQL/DTO types as needed)

## Error Handling

- Wrap checked exceptions in `RuntimeException` in command `run()` methods
- Use `IllegalArgumentException` / `IllegalStateException` for invalid input or configuration
- Log errors with `logger.error()` before returning null or continuing in non-critical paths
- Fail fast in configuration classes on invalid credentials/settings

## Logging

- Use `org.jboss.logging.Logger` (constructor-injected)
- Use format methods: `logger.infof()`, `logger.warnf()`, `logger.error()`

## Conventions

- Every package should have a `package-info.java`
- **Commands:** `@CommandLine.Command` on command classes; options via `@CommandLine.Option`; root command aggregates subcommands in `GitHubCommand`
- **GraphQL:** hand-written client/wrapper classes in **`clients`** (e.g. **`GitHubGraphQLClient`**); **generated** types under **`clients.graphql.generated`** (do not hand-edit)
- **MicroProfile REST:** only if reintroduced — `@RegisterRestClient` on interfaces in `clients.rest` (not used by collect-stats today)
